                                            [content] => I'm a masochist with OCD and too much disk space. I process them one by one. I had planned to write down my workflow, but then I got hooked on Lightroom and it changed. First I go through and put keywords on everything, tagging obviously bad photos like horrible focus or extremely bad lighting. Next I go through again with nothing visible but each image and tag the ones I want to process plus any more bad images. I delete the bad ones, save all the metadata, and put the tagged pictures in a collection. Then I'm ready to go through the collection and process each photo. Today I took 32 pictures of a cardinal and processed only 5 of them.
