                                                )

                                            [content] => Fred Brundick - when I import I go to the "Current Import" collection (a special folder near the Quick Collection). It's configured with a filter for the Attribute (pick/unflagged/rejected and ratings) so that only pick and unflagged are shown, but rejected photos are immediately hidden from view. Then I go thru the photos using keyboard controls. Immediate keepers are (P)icked, obvious crap (as you said, horrible focus etc.) are rejected (X).

Then I change the Attribute filter to only show rejected photos and delete all of them. After that, I switch to the picks and start processing them. That leaves me with a selection of good photos to concentrate my efforts on rather quickly - instead of wasting time with keywording photos that I will most likely not show, maybe not process, or delete.
