                                            [content] => I've been keeping my friendships on FB strict since day 1. I set up my own private  Facebook policy from the start which is fairly simple: "Don't friend anyone on FB that you haven't met in real life and shared a memorable and positive experience with". In this way FB become more of a close family with people you enjoy or like. Of course there are a few exceptions from this rule, since i have met fantastic people on-line but still haven't had the opportunity to meet them in real life yet. I wish one day i'm able to do so. The point is; it pays of in the long run to be extremely selective being able to slowly build a network of people you trust and share some basic values with. In the same way i've had only a fraction of friends that have unfriended me on Facebook which in turn shows that the bonds are real. 
And further more it seem to prove the obvious; 'There is No Quality in Numbers' :)
