                                            [content] => Not to be picky but it came out in 69 actually. My parents took me to see it and I was 8 at the time. Of course I liked it because it was a Western, but I also discovered I liked Katherine Ross also..and kind of grew up quickly discovering I liked Katherine Ross and others like her. There is the classic scene when she enters her cabin and Redford is there and points his gun at her and tells her to take it off..slowly. She does and then embraces him. I still to this day remember the theater being so quiet and then I yelled out to my dad "What are they doing Dad ?" Had to be there I guess, but it is a family joke. I guess the people around us broke up in laughter.
